# UI/UX Conventions

The visual language is defined by tokens in [src/app/globals.css](../../src/app/globals.css) and primitives in [src/components/ui/](../../src/components/ui/). Always reach for those before hand-rolling Tailwind classes.

Full token reference: [docs/DESIGN_TOKENS.md](../../docs/DESIGN_TOKENS.md).

## Layout

- The app shell (`AppShell`) provides a sidebar, top bar with breadcrumbs, `max-w-7xl` centering, `py-8 pb-24` padding, and scrolling via `overflow-y-auto` on `<main>`.
- `html` and `body` have `overflow: hidden; height: 100%` — never rely on body scroll.
- Pages render inside the shell; don't add their own max-width or horizontal padding.

## Color tokens

Prefer the **semantic** tokens over raw `gray-*`:

| Use | Class |
|---|---|
| Page background | `bg-bg-app` |
| Card / row surface | `bg-surface` |
| Toolbar / table header | `bg-surface-muted` |
| Inset well / segmented track | `bg-surface-sunken` |
| Default border | `border-border` |
| Input border / strong divider | `border-border-strong` |
| Hairline divider | `border-border-subtle` |
| Body text | `text-text-primary` |
| Subtitle / labels | `text-text-secondary` |
| Metadata | `text-text-muted` |
| Disabled / placeholder | `text-text-disabled` |

Signals: use `success`, `warning`, `danger`, `info`, `accent` scales, **not** raw `green-*`, `amber-*`, `red-*`, `blue-*`, `purple-*`.

Avoid `text-gray-400` for body content — it fails WCAG AA (2.86:1 on white). Use `text-text-muted` (`#6b7280`, 4.83:1) instead.

## Typography ramp

Use the typography tokens defined in `globals.css`. Do not invent text sizes inline.

| Token | Use |
|---|---|
| `text-display-lg` | Hero numbers / dashboard headlines |
| `text-display` | Page titles (auto-applied by `PageHeader`) |
| `text-h2` | Section headings |
| `text-h3` | Card / `FormSection` titles |
| `text-body-lg` | Lead body |
| `text-body` | Default body, labels, table cells |
| `text-caption` | Metadata, helper text, table headers |

## Cards

Use the `Card` primitive over the raw `rounded-lg border bg-white shadow-xs` snippet:

Each primitive is imported directly from its own module (e.g. `@/components/ui/card`). There is no `@/components/ui` barrel — import the thing from where it lives.

```tsx
import { Card } from '@/components/ui/card';

<Card>
  <h2 className="text-h3 font-semibold">Distribution</h2>
  ...
</Card>
```

Use `<StatCard>` for KPIs.

## Buttons

There is exactly **one** button system. Reach for these in priority order:

| Need | Primitive |
|---|---|
| Action button | `<Button variant="primary | secondary | ghost | danger | link" />` |
| Navigation CTA | `<LinkButton href="/..." iconLeft={<PlusIcon />} />` |
| Square icon button (table actions, toolbar) | `<IconButton label="..." icon={<TrashIcon />} />` |

Never write inline `<button className="bg-primary-600 ...">`. The legacy `PrimaryButton`/`PrimaryLinkButton` from `@/components/page-header` are deprecated wrappers that delegate to `Button`/`LinkButton` — prefer the new names.

## Tabs and segmented controls

| Pattern | Primitive |
|---|---|
| Page-level navigation between views | `<Tabs items={[...]} active={active} />` (underline) |
| View-mode switch (List/Matrix, source filter) | `<SegmentedControl options={[...]} value={...} onChange={...} />` |

Never re-implement `border-b-2` or `bg-white shadow-sm` toggle markup inline.

## Badges

The single `Badge` primitive from `@/components/ui/badge` replaces every pill:

```tsx
<Badge tone="success" variant="soft">Reviewed</Badge>
<Badge tone="info" variant="outline">Preset</Badge>
<Badge tone="accent">Multi-Strategy</Badge>
```

Tones: `neutral | info | success | warning | danger | accent`. Variants: `soft | solid | outline`. Sizes: `sm | md`.

`StatusBadge` (active/inactive/deleted) is a domain wrapper over `Badge` — keep using it when applicable.

## Spinners and icons

- Always import icons from `@/components/ui/icons` (a curated, aliased re-export of lucide). Do not import directly from `lucide-react`, and do not paste inline SVG path data.
- Use `<Spinner size="xs | sm | md | lg" />` for loading indicators. Never paste the spinner SVG inline.

## Forms

- Page structure: `<PageHeader>` → `<ResourceFormHeader>` → `<FormSection title="..." description="...">` per logical section.
- Use `<FormSection>` instead of stacking unlabeled `<div>` sections in long forms.
- Use `<ErrorCard>` for inline form errors.
- Place save/create buttons in `PageHeader.actions` (top-right), not sticky footers.

## Confirmations and toasts

- Replace `window.confirm()` with `useConfirm()`:
  ```tsx
  const confirm = useConfirm();
  const ok = await confirm({ title: 'Delete?', tone: 'danger' });
  ```
- Use `toast.success()` / `toast.error()` / `toast.warning()` for action feedback. Never silently `catch { /* ignore */ }` — surface failures.

## Filters above lists

Use `<FilterBar>` and `<FilterSearch>` from `@/components/ui/filter-bar` to build filter rows that aren't inside a `DataTable` toolbar. Inside `DataTable`, the existing `SearchBar`/`FilterPills`/`SelectAllCheckbox` continue to be the source of truth.

